org.opendaylight.controller.containermanager

Class ContainerFlowConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opendaylight.controller.configuration.ConfigurationObject
      • org.opendaylight.controller.containermanager.ContainerFlowConfig
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ContainerFlowConfig
extends ConfigurationObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Flow Specification Java Object for Container Manager Represents a container flow configuration information for Container Manager. Objects of this class are serialized to and de-serialized from binary files through java serialization API when saving to/reading from Container manager startup configuration file.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • getMatches

        public java.util.List<Match> getMatches()
        Returns the matches. If unidirectional flag is set, there will be only one match per vlan in the list If unidirectional flag is unset there will be two matches per vlan in the list, only if the specified flow has an intrinsic direction. For Ex. if the cFlow only has the protocol field configured, no matter if unidirectional flag is set or not, only one match per vlan will be returned The client just has to iterate over the returned list
        Returns:
        the matches
